						               													<description>One minute isn't the world, is it? Do you feel the same way even if you only have so much time to memorize every detail of a picture? Exciting challenges await!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Memorace board game develops not only memory but also general knowledge and literacy in a fun way: this time you can marvel at natural phenomena. Get involved as soon as possible, learn playfully!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Along with the challenges, the game develops logical thinking, memory and attention - all in an interactive and fun way.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Draw a card and place it in front of you.&amp;#10;     Turn the clock over and try to remember as many details as possible while the sand is spreading - this is about 10 seconds.&amp;#10;     Roll the dice!&amp;#10;     If you rolled a 1, you must answer the thought-provoking puzzle on the front page. Look at the picture and count or guess correctly!&amp;#10;     If you did not roll a 1, turn the card over and answer the question on the back next to the rolled number. These will test your memory, but if you pay attention, you will definitely know the answer!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
